                            <comment id="14495204" author="avandana" created="Wed, 15 Apr 2015 00:28:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tedyu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tedyu&quot;&gt;Ted Yu&lt;/a&gt; &amp;#8211; The idea of updating quota only on successful merge sounds good, as I think concurrent merge operations would be rare unlike splits. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;looking at the v2 patch, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;if (code == TransitionCode.MERGED &amp;amp;&amp;amp; org.apache.commons.lang.StringUtils.isEmpty(errorMsg)) {&lt;br/&gt;
+        try &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;Unknown macro: {
+          regionStateListener.onRegionMerged(hri);
+        }&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt; catch (IOException exp) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;Unknown macro: {
+          errorMsg = StringUtils.stringifyException(exp);
+        }&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;+      }&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;shouldn&apos;t that be under MERGED case rather than MERGE_REVERTED ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14495505" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Wed, 15 Apr 2015 01:11:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The intention is to put call to listener after the call to onRegionMerge().&lt;br/&gt;
This aligns with the formation in master branch. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
